; Regression test for issue #655: -Q/--download should trigger price
; downloads even when no existing price is available in the history.
; https://github.com/ledger/ledger/issues/655
;
; The bug was that check_for_updated_price() was only called when
; find_price() returned a non-null result.  When no price existed
; at all (no P directive, no implicit exchange rate), no download
; was attempted despite --download being enabled.
;
; This test has a commodity (AAPL) with no price history at all --
; both postings are in AAPL so no exchange rate is established.
; The mock getquote script returns "2024/06/15 AAPL $150.00".
; Without the fix, --market would show "10 AAPL" (no conversion).

2024/01/15 Receive Stock Gift
    Assets:Brokerage        10 AAPL
    Income:Gifts            -10 AAPL

test bal --market --download --getquote $sourcepath/test/scripts/mock-getquote.sh Assets:Brokerage
            $1500.00  Assets:Brokerage
end test
